folder: St. Raymond's Avenue & Odell Street, Bronx, NY
original_title: Bronx: St. Raymond's Avenue - Odell Street
text:
St. Raymond Avenue, south Side, from Odell Street to Olmstead Ave., showing Public School No. 106.
Board of Education of the City of New York
Credit Line Imperative.  Early 1930's

folder: Odell Street & St. Raymond Avenue, Bronx, NY
original_title: Bronx: Odell Street - St. Raymond Avenue
text:
Odell Street, north from St. Raymond Avenue. On the right are buildings of the Bronx Gas and Electric Company. Part of this area, particularly that on the west side of the street, later became part of the huge housing project of the Metropolitan Life Insurance Company.

April 10, 1938
P. L. Sperr
